%% Configuration management flow
%% Admin -> WfmConfig -> Aurora/COR/MyGlobal -> services pick up on refresh
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Admin as Platform Admin
    participant WC as WfmConfig<br/>(C# / ASP.NET Core)
    participant JWT as JWT middleware
    participant SVC as Service layer
    participant DA as DataAccess (Dapper)
    participant AUR as Aurora<br/>(TenantStatus, Clusters,<br/>Settings, Adherence)
    participant COR as COR DB<br/>(divisions/BUs)
    participant MG as MyGlobal DB
    participant SC as StateCollector
    participant SP as StatePublisher
    participant IP as IntervalPublisher
    participant ES as EtlScheduler

    Admin->>WC: PUT /api/tenantStatus<br/>{SegmentedByDivisions, DivisionIdSet, ...}
    WC->>JWT: validate Bearer
    JWT-->>WC: ok (custom signature validator)
    WC->>SVC: authorize + validate
    SVC->>DA: QueryAsync("TenantStatus_Put", ..., StoredProcedure)
    DA->>AUR: CALL TenantStatus_Put(...)
    AUR-->>DA: success
    DA-->>SVC: result
    SVC-->>WC: response
    WC-->>Admin: 200 OK + JSON

    Note over SC,IP: Periodic config refresh per service
    SC->>WC: GET /api/tenantStatus, /api/clusters
    SP->>WC: GET /api/tenantStatus
    IP->>WC: GET /api/tenantStatus<br/>(SegmentedByDivisions routing)

    Note over ES: Reads Aurora directly<br/>(no WfmConfig hop)
    ES->>AUR: CALL Interval_GetClusters
    AUR-->>ES: list (new clusters appear on next 60s tick)
